#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld
msgid "# Subset World\n"
"\n"
"In Set World, you learned that sets are predicates and membership is\n"
"predicate evaluation. Now you will learn the two fundamental\n"
"relationships between sets: **subset** (آ§0) and **equality** (آ§1).\n"
"\n"
"A **subset** proof آ§2 means: for every element, if it is in آ§3\n"
"then it is in آ§4. The proof shape is always آ§5 â€” fix an\n"
"element, assume it is in the smaller set, then show it is in the\n"
"larger set.\n"
"\n"
"A **set equality** proof آ§6 means: the two sets have exactly the\n"
"same elements. There are two routes:\n"
"- **Extensionality** (آ§7): prove آ§8 directly\n"
"- **Double containment** (آ§9): prove آ§10 and\n"
"  آ§11 separately\n"
"\n"
"By the end of this world, you will:\n"
"- Prove subset relations with the آ§12 pattern\n"
"- Handle the boundary cases آ§13 and آ§14\n"
"- Use subset hypotheses as functions\n"
"- Disprove false subset claims by contradiction\n"
"- Chain subset proofs transitively\n"
"- Prove set equality via آ§15 (extensionality)\n"
"- Prove set equality via آ§16 (double containment)\n"
"- Prove set non-equality by finding a contradictory witness\n"
"- Prove proper subset (آ§17) by combining آ§18 and آ§19\n"
"- Use آ§20 to unwrap set notation on hypotheses\n"
"\n"
"You will also gain a new tactic (آ§21) and a new proof strategy\n"
"(double containment) that you will use throughout the rest of this\n"
"course.\n"
"\n"
"**New tools in this world**:\n"
"- آ§22 â€” unwrap a hypothesis to a definitionally equal form\n"
"- آ§23 â€” reduce set equality to element-wise membership\n"
"- آ§24 â€” derive equality from mutual subsets"
msgstr ""

