#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L10_ExtIntro
msgid "# Extensionality: When Two Sets Are Equal\n"
"\n"
"Two sets are equal when they have exactly the same elements:\n"
"\n"
"آ§0\n"
"\n"
"This is the **Axiom of Extensionality** â€” one of the foundational\n"
"axioms of set theory. It says that a set is nothing more than its\n"
"elements: two sets with the same members are the same set, regardless\n"
"of how they are described. The tactic آ§1\n"
"converts a set equality goal into: for each آ§2, prove the membership\n"
"biconditional آ§3.\n"
"\n"
"After آ§4, the goal becomes an آ§5. Use آ§6 to split it\n"
"into two implications (forward and backward), then prove each direction.\n"
"\n"
"After آ§7, you will see the آ§8 (focus dot) for the first time.\n"
"When Lean creates multiple subgoals, آ§9 **focuses** on one subgoal at\n"
"a time. Write آ§10 to apply آ§11 to the current subgoal only.\n"
"After that subgoal is closed, the next آ§12 picks up the next subgoal.\n"
"Think of آ§13 as \"now working on this case.\"\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that آ§14.\n"
"\n"
"The conjunction آ§15 is equivalent to just آ§16 because\n"
"آ§17 already implies آ§18. So the second condition is redundant.\n"
"\n"
"This level is longer than previous ones â€” the proof has several steps.\n"
"Do not worry: each step is guided by hints, and the math is simple.\n"
"The length comes from the proof structure, not from difficulty.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. آ§19 â€” reduce to membership biconditional\n"
"2. آ§20 â€” split the آ§21 into two directions\n"
"3. **Forward** (آ§22): given آ§23, extract آ§24\n"
"4. **Backward** (آ§25): given آ§26, build آ§27"
msgstr ""

