"\n"
"Time to combine everything. You are given an abstract predicate آ§0\n"
"on natural numbers, with two hypotheses:\n"
"\n"
"- آ§1 â€” every even number satisfies آ§2\n"
"- آ§3 â€” every number satisfying آ§4 is even\n"
"\n"
"Together these say: آ§5 holds for exactly the even numbers.\n"
"\n"
"You must prove two things:\n"
"1. آ§6 â€” 4 is in the p-set (because 4 is even)\n"
"2. آ§7 â€” 3 is NOT in the p-set (because 3 is odd)\n"
"\n"
"This combines:\n"
"- Membership via hypothesis (Levels 1â€“2, 4): use آ§8 then\n"
"  provide a witness for آ§9\n"
"- Non-membership via contradiction (Levels 3, 5): assume آ§10,\n"
"  derive آ§11 from آ§12, destructure the existential with\n"
"  آ§13, then reach an arithmetic contradiction\n"
"\n"
"Start with آ§14 to split the conjunction."
