#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L09_NonArithSubset
msgid "# Subsets Are About Predicates, Not Just Arithmetic\n"
"\n"
"Every subset proof so far ended with آ§0 â€” because every set was\n"
"defined by an arithmetic inequality like آ§1 or آ§2.\n"
"\n"
"But آ§3 is not about arithmetic. It is about **predicates**: آ§4\n"
"means that the predicate defining آ§5 implies the predicate defining آ§6.\n"
"The closing move depends entirely on what those predicates are.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, the sets are defined by abstract predicates آ§7 and آ§8\n"
"on a general type آ§9 (not necessarily آ§10). You are given\n"
"آ§11 â€” a pointwise implication between the\n"
"predicates. Your task is to prove the subset inclusion.\n"
"\n"
"The proof follows the same آ§12 pattern. But the closing move\n"
"is not آ§13 â€” it is آ§14, applying the given implication.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. آ§15 â€” assume آ§16 is in the left set (i.e., آ§17 holds)\n"
"2. آ§18 â€” apply the implication to get آ§19"
msgstr ""

