#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L12_SetNonEquality
msgid "You proved your first set **non-equality**! The proof structure was:\n"
"\n"
"1. **Assume** the sets are equal (آ§0)\n"
"2. **Exhibit** a witness element (3)\n"
"3. **Transport** membership using the equality (آ§1)\n"
"4. **Derive contradiction** from the impossible conclusion (آ§2)\n"
"\n"
"Compare this with Level 7 (disproving آ§3):\n"
"\n"
"| Goal | Assume | Witness | Contradiction from |\n"
"|---|---|---|---|\n"
"| آ§4 | آ§5 | element in آ§6 but not آ§7 | applying آ§8 to witness |\n"
"| آ§9 | آ§10 | element in one but not other | rewriting with آ§11 |\n"
"\n"
"Both use the same strategy â€” assume and contradict â€” but the mechanism\n"
"differs. For آ§12, you apply the subset hypothesis as a function. For\n"
"آ§13, you rewrite with the equality hypothesis to transport membership.\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary math: \"Suppose آ§14. Then\n"
"آ§15 (since آ§16 and the sets are equal).\n"
"But آ§17 is false. Contradiction.\""
msgstr ""

